# ChineseLanguageEngage Monorepo

Monorepo for game mods that add Chinese language-learning support. The repo exists so that all games live under one GitHub page; there is no meaningful cross-dependency between individual game directories.

## Structure

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `cedict/` | Shared CEDICT dictionary data (runtime dependency for all mods) |
| `shadowrun-returns/` | Shadowrun Returns — contains `mod/` (BepInEx plugin) and `preprocessor/` (Python pipeline) |

## Conventions

- Game directories use kebab-case (e.g. `shadowrun-returns`, `baldurs-gate-2`).
- Each game has `mod/` (runtime plugin, own `.sln`) and `preprocessor/` (Python, depends on `pinyiniser`).
- CEDICT is shared; preprocessors are game-specific (different file formats per game).

## Workspace Workflow

**Open individual game directories in Cursor, not the monorepo root.** Each game directory (e.g. `shadowrun-returns/`) has its own `.cursor/rules/` with game-specific context. Opening the game directory as the workspace root ensures Cursor picks up those rules instead of the monorepo-level ones.

The monorepo root is for repo-wide concerns (README, CI, CEDICT). Day-to-day development on a specific game should always use that game's directory as the workspace.
